(2, 28, 0, 'Cakephp3 Save Many To Many Table Example Tags', 'cakephp3-save-many-to-many-table-example-tags__1550660762', 'Gabriel Kolbe', 'gabriel-kolbe__1546695864', 0, 0, 1, '<p>I am trying to create a multi select drop down in Cakephp3. Then update a many to many</p><p>I have a post table and tags table and a post_tags table the models have the following foreign keys</p><pre><code>PostsTable  $this-&gt;hasMany( PostTags , [        foreignKey  =&gt;  post_id   ]);      TagsTable  $this-&gt;hasMany( PostTags , [        foreignKey  =&gt;  tag_id   ]);    PostTagsTable  $this-&gt;belongsTo( Tags , [       foreignKey  =&gt;  tag_id ,        joinType  =&gt;  INNER   ]);  </code></pre><p>the post tags table has a post_id and tag_id</p><p>in my post add view I have</p><p>echo $this-&gt;Form-&gt;input(&#39;tags&#39;, [&#39;class&#39;=&gt;&#39;form-control&#39;, &#39;id&#39;=&gt;&#39;select4&#39;, &#39;label&#39; =&gt; false, &#39;options&#39; =&gt; $tags, &#39;multiple&#39; =&gt; &#39;multiple&#39;]);</p><p>When I debug in the controller I get</p><pre><code> tags  =&gt; [      (int) 0 =&gt;  1 ,      (int) 1 =&gt;  2   ],  </code></pre><p>When I look on stack overflow it seems I need to have this: ( I am not 100% sure this is correct) A:</p><pre><code>$data = [       tags  =&gt; [          [ id  =&gt; 1],      [ id  =&gt; 2]      ]  ]  </code></pre><p>I tried looping through the $tags like but the debug results are pretty much the same: Looping like this</p><pre><code>&lt;div  \'input select\'&gt;  &lt;input type=\'hidden\' name=\'tags\'  value=\'\' \'select4_\'&gt;  &lt;select name=\'tags[]\' multiple=\'multiple\'  \'select4\' size=\'7\'&gt;  &lt;?php  echo  &lt;option  \'tag1\' value=\'tag1\'&gt;option 1&lt;/option&gt; ;   echo  &lt;option  \'tag2\' value=\'tag2\' &gt;option 2&lt;/option&gt; ;  ?&gt;  &lt;/select&gt;  &lt;/div&gt;  </code></pre><p>I will get</p><pre><code> tags  =&gt; [      (int) 0 =&gt;  tag1 ,      (int) 1 =&gt;  tag2   ],  </code></pre><p>Apparently I need to pass the values as shown in A: to the controller and then do</p><pre><code>$post = $this-&gt;Posts-&gt;patchEntity($post, $this-&gt;request-&gt;data, [ associated  =&gt; [ Tags ]]);  </code></pre><p>To make it all work. I would appreciate some help on this as I have been struggeling for days with this. Thanks</p>', 0, 417, 'CakePHP,PHP', 0, 0, '2019-02-20', '2022-01-04'),
(5, 1, 4, 'answer', 'how-to-wrap-text-around-an-image-using-htmlcss-is-there-a-better-way-ij__1550829048', 'Project Owner', 'admin', 0, NULL, NULL, '<p><strong>TRY this</strong></p><p><strong>TEXT</strong></p><pre><code>&lt;img src=\"https://www.skillbooker.com/img/lego_305.jpg\" /&gt;\r\n&lt;h1&gt;Works for me&lt;/h1&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetuer adipiscing elit. Nam cursus. Morbi ut mi. Nullam enim leo, egestas id, condimentum at,&lt;/p&gt;</code></pre><p><strong>CSS</strong></p><pre><code>img {\r\n    float: left;\r\n    margin: 0 20px 20px 0;\r\n    width: 150px;\r\n    height: 150px;\r\n}\r\n\r\np {\r\n    text-align: justify;\r\n    text-indent: 2em;\r\n}</code></pre><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 3, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-02-22', '2019-02-22'),
(4, 28, 0, 'How To Wrap Text Around An Image Using Html/css - Is There A Better Way ?', 'how-to-wrap-text-around-an-image-using-htmlcss-is-there-a-better-way-ij__1550829048', 'Gabriel Kolbe', 'gabriel-kolbe__1546695864', 0, 0, 1, '<p>you have to&nbsp;<code>float</code>&nbsp;your image container as follows:</p><p><strong>HTML</strong></p><pre><code>&lt;div id=\"container\"&gt;\r\n    &lt;div id=\"floated\"&gt;...some other random text&lt;/div&gt;\r\n    ...\r\n    some random text\r\n    ...\r\n&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre><p><strong>CSS</strong></p><pre><code>#container{\r\n    width: 400px;\r\n    background: yellow;\r\n}\r\n#floated{\r\n    float: left;\r\n    width: 150px;\r\n    background: red;\r\n}</code></pre><p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, 285, 'none', 0, 1, '2019-02-22', '2022-01-04'),
(6, 28, 0, 'How Can I Protect My Site From Software Than Scan And Rip My Website - Software Like Httrack Or Winhttptrack Or Other Ones', 'how-can-i-protect-my-site-from-software-than-scan-and-rip-my-website-software-like-httrack-or-winhttptrack-or-other-ones__1550838649', 'Gabriel Kolbe', 'gabriel-kolbe__1546695864', 0, 0, 1, '<p>After search I found the answer so here it is for anyone else looking for an answer, it is bar impossible to stop humans doing it but software you can stop - to a degree.</p><p>1) In .htaccess</p><pre><code>RewriteCond %{HTTP_USER_AGENT} ^HTTrack [OR]\r\nRewriteCond %{HTTP_USER_AGENT} ^SiteSucker [OR]\r\nRewriteCond %{HTTP_USER_AGENT} ^WebZip [OR]\r\nRewriteCond %{HTTP_USER_AGENT} ^WebCopier [OR]\r\nRewriteCond %{HTTP_USER_AGENT} ^Zeus\r\nRewriteRule ^.*$ no_download.html [L]\r\n</code></pre><p>Add additional Spam_bot by adding&nbsp;<code>RewriteCond %{HTTP_USER_AGENT} ^Other_Spam_bot</code>&nbsp;after&nbsp;<code>[OR]</code></p><p>(2) In robots.txt</p><pre><code>User-agent: AhrefsBot\r\nUser-agent: Baiduspider\r\nUser-agent: EasouSpider\r\nUser-agent: Ezooms\r\nUser-agent: YandexBot\r\nUser-agent: MJ12bot\r\nUser-agent: SiteSucker\r\nUser-agent: HTTrack\r\nDisallow: /\r\n</code></pre><p>Add additional Spam_bot by adding&nbsp;<code>User-agent: Other_Spam_bot</code>&nbsp;before&nbsp;<code>Disallow: /</code></p>', 1, 416, 'HTML', 0, 0, '2019-02-22', '2022-01-04'),
(7, 1, 0, 'Extend Upload Time And File Size On Xampp So That You Don\'t Get Time Out', 'extend-upload-time-and-file-size-on-xampp-so-that-you-dont-get-time-out__1552403841', 'Nice  Guy', 'admin', 0, 0, 1, '<p>Best way I could find is by editing the php.ini file in xampp/php</p><p>Find the following locations and make the changes by extending the times and file sizes</p><p><br />post_max_size = 999M&nbsp;<br />upload_max_filesize = 99M&nbsp;<br />max_execution_time = 9999&nbsp;<br />max_input_time = 9999&nbsp;<br />memory_limit = 9999M&nbsp;</p><p>restart Apache for the settings to take effect !</p>', 1, 245, 'xampp,Apache,PHP', 0, 0, '2019-03-12', '2022-01-02'),
(8, 1, 0, 'Get This Error When Using Cakephp 3 You Must Enable The Intl Extension To Use Cakephp', 'get-this-error-when-using-cakephp-3-you-must-enable-the-intl-extension-to-use-cakephp__1552404839', 'Nice  Guy', 'admin', 0, 0, 1, '<p><strong>Solution Xampp (Windows)</strong></p><ol><li>Open&nbsp;/xampp/php/php.ini</li><li>Change&nbsp;;extension=php_intl.dll&nbsp;to&nbsp;extension=php_intl.dll&nbsp;(remove the semicolon)</li><li>Copy all the&nbsp;/xamp/php/ic*.dll&nbsp;files to&nbsp;/xampp/apache/bin</li><li>Restart apache in the Xampp control panel</li></ol><p><strong>Solution&nbsp;Linux&nbsp;(thanks to Annamalai Somasundaram)</strong></p><ol><li>Install the php5-intl extension&nbsp;sudo apt-get install php5-intl</li><li>Alternatively use&nbsp;sudo yum install php5-intl&nbsp;if you are on CentOS or Fedora.</li><li>Restart apache&nbsp;sudo service apache2 restart</li></ol><p><strong>Solution&nbsp;Mac/OSX&nbsp;(homebrew)&nbsp;(thanks to deizel)</strong></p><ol><li>Install the php5-intl extension&nbsp;brew install php56-intl</li><li>If you get&nbsp;No available formula for php56-intl&nbsp;follow&nbsp;these&nbsp;instructions.</li><li>Restart apache&nbsp;sudo apachectl restart</li></ol>', 1, 987, 'xampp,Git,Apache,Linux,PHP', 0, 0, '2019-03-12', '2022-01-02'),
(10, 28, 0, 'Finding The Selected Values In A Multi Select Drop Down With Javascript Or Jquery', 'finding-the-selected-values-in-a-multi-select-drop-down-with-javascript-or-jquery__1552644434', 'Gabriel Kolbe', 'gabriel-kolbe__1546695864', 0, 0, 1, '<pre><code>function findvalues() {      var str = document.getElementById(&#39;findvaluesid&#39;);      var str = [];      while(str.selectedIndex != -1) {        if(str.selectedIndex != 0) str.push(str.options[str.selectedIndex].value);         str.options[str.selectedIndex].selected = false;     }       console.log(str);  }</code></pre><p>This works right, but as you can see from the code this line:</p><pre><code>str.options[str.selectedIndex].selected = false;</code></pre><p>Is doing a deselecting of the value.</p><p>Now, I do not want to deselect the values. If I uncomment that line in the code, the code will run forever.</p><p>Is there any more refined and sophisticated solution for retrieving multiple values from a select tag using Javascript?</p>', 1, 240, 'Javascript ,JQuery', 0, 1, '2019-03-15', '2021-12-29'),
(11, 1, 10, 'answer', 'finding-the-selected-values-in-a-multi-select-drop-down-with-javascript-or-jquery__1552644434', 'Nice  Guy', 'admin', 0, NULL, NULL, '<p>Try this</p><pre><code>function findvalues() {\r\n    var str = document.getElementById(\"findvaluesid\");\r\n    var str = [];\r\n    for (var i = 0; i &lt; str.length; i++) {\r\n        if (str.options[i].selected) str.push(str.options[i].value);\r\n    }\r\n    console.log(str);\r\n}?</code></pre>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-03-15', '2019-03-15'),
(12, 1, 0, 'Redirect From Http To Https Using .htacces In Cakephp 3', 'redirect-from-http-to-https-using-htacces-in-cakephp-3__1552998908', 'Nice  Guy', 'admin', 0, 0, 1, '<p>My app is hosted on heroku, and I am using Cakephp API. I want it to be redirect to&nbsp;<a href=&#39;https://www/&#39;>https://www</a>. and enforcing the www. subdomain.</p><p>And, they have two domains point to the same app.</p><p>I have the follow code, in the /app/.htaccess</p><pre><code>RewriteEngine on    RewriteBase /    #apply if no https  RewriteCond %{HTTPS} off      #Ignore when is local env or any staging env  RewriteCond %{HTTP_HOST} !^local(.*) [NC]  RewriteCond %{HTTP_HOST} !^(.*)heroku(.*) [NC]    RewriteRule .* https://%{HTTP_HOST}%{REQUEST_URI} [NE,L,R=301]    #apply if https  RewriteCond %{HTTPS} on  #Ignore when is local env or any staging env or subdoamin is www.  RewriteCond %{HTTP_HOST} !^www. [NC]  RewriteCond %{HTTP_HOST} !^local(.*) [NC]  RewriteCond %{HTTP_HOST} !^(.*)heroku(.*) [NC]  RewriteRule .* https://www.%{HTTP_HOST}%{REQUEST_URI} [NE,L,R=301]    #default from cakephp  RewriteRule ^$ webroot/ [L]  RewriteRule (.*) webroot/$1 [L]</code></pre><p>I have the follow code, in the /app/webroot/.htaccess</p><pre><code>RewriteEngine On    RewriteBase /    #redirect any request from .poa.br to .com.br  RewriteCond %{HTTP_HOST} ^(.*)example.poa.br$ [NC]  RewriteRule ^(.*)$ https://www.example.com.br/$1 [NE,R=301,L]    RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-d  RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-f  RewriteRule ^ index.php [L]</code></pre><p>But it doesn&#39;t work. Just the follows requests are redirect to&nbsp;<a href=&#39;https://www.example.com.br/&#39;>https://www.example.com.br</a>:</p><pre><code>https://www.example.com.br   https://www.example.poa.br   http://www.example.poa.br </code></pre><p>This option go to domain, but without https prefix.</p><pre><code>http://www.example.com.br </code></pre><p>The other options doesn&#39;t work (return DNS_PROBE_FINISHED_NXDOMAIN):</p><pre><code>https://example.com.br   http://example.com.br   https://example.poa.br   http://example.poa.br</code></pre>', 1, 1064, 'CakePHP,PHP', 0, 1, '2019-03-19', '2022-01-04'),
(13, 28, 12, 'answer', 'redirect-from-http-to-https-using-htacces-in-cakephp-3__1552998908', 'Gabriel Kolbe', 'gabriel-kolbe__1546695864', 0, NULL, NULL, '<p>I struggled with this in cakephp3. My solution was to change the first .htaccess file from</p><pre><code>&lt;IfModule mod_rewrite.c&gt;\r\n    RewriteEngine on\r\n    RewriteRule    ^$    webroot/    [L]\r\n    RewriteRule    (.*)   webroot/$1    [L]\r\n&lt;/IfModule&gt;</code></pre><p>TO</p><pre><code>&lt;IfModule mod_rewrite.c&gt;\r\n    RewriteEngine on\r\n    RewriteCond %{HTTP:X-Forwarded-Proto} =http\r\n    RewriteRule ^ https://%{HTTP_HOST}%{REQUEST_URI} [L,R=302]\r\n    RewriteRule    ^$    webroot/    [L]\r\n    RewriteRule    (.*) webroot/$1    [L]\r\n&lt;/IfModule&gt;</code></pre><p>Notice the 302, the reason I struggled is that the .htaccess got cached and made testing very difficult, I even went as far as delete all the cakephp code in the index.php in the webroot and just echo out &#39;test&#39; Once I got it working I changed the 302 to 301 so that the .htaccess can hard cache in the browser. ( To test if values like HTTP:X-Forwarded-Proto exist I var_dump($_SERVER) in the index.php file )</p><p>IF you are on a server without HTTP:X-Forwarded-Proto</p><pre><code>&lt;IfModule mod_rewrite.c&gt;\r\n    RewriteEngine On \r\n    RewriteCond %{HTTPS} !=on\r\n    RewriteRule ^ https://%{HTTP_HOST}%{REQUEST_URI} [L,R=302]\r\n\r\n    RewriteRule    ^$    webroot/    [L]\r\n    RewriteRule    (.*) webroot/$1    [L]\r\n&lt;/IfModule&gt;</code></pre>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-03-19', '2019-03-19'),
(14, 1, 0, 'Find The Day Of The Week From A Date Using Php?', 'find-the-day-of-the-week-from-a-date-using-phpij__1553098378', 'Nice  Guy', 'admin', 0, 0, 1, '<p>f I&#39;ve got a&nbsp;<code>$date</code>&nbsp;<code>YYYY-mm-dd</code>&nbsp;and want to get a specific&nbsp;<code>$day</code>&nbsp;(specified by 0 (sunday) to 6 (saturday)) of the week that&nbsp;<code>YYYY-mm-dd</code>&nbsp;is in.</p><p>For example, if I got&nbsp;<code>2012-10-11</code>&nbsp;as&nbsp;<code>$date</code>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<code>5</code>&nbsp;as&nbsp;<code>$day</code>, I want to get&nbsp;<code>2012-10-12</code>, if I&#39;ve got&nbsp;<code>0</code>as&nbsp;<code>$day</code>,&nbsp;<code>2012-10-14</code><br /><br />Most of you misunderstood it. I got some date,&nbsp;<code>$date</code>&nbsp;and want to get a day specified by 0-6 of the same week&nbsp;<code>$date</code>&nbsp;is in.</p><p>So no, I don&#39;t want the day of&nbsp;<code>$date</code>...</p>', 1, 219, 'PHP', 0, 1, '2019-03-20', '2022-01-02'),
(15, 28, 14, 'answer', 'find-the-day-of-the-week-from-a-date-using-phpij__1553098378', 'Gabriel Kolbe', 'gabriel-kolbe__1546695864', 0, NULL, NULL, '<p>I think you want is the following</p><pre><code>$dayofweek = date(\'w\', strtotime($date));\r\n$result    = date(\'Y-m-d\', strtotime(($day - $dayofweek).\' day\', strtotime($date)));</code></pre>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-03-20', '2019-03-20'),
(16, 1, 0, 'Cakephp - How Do I Render A View In A Controller From Another Controller', 'cakephp-how-do-i-render-a-view-in-a-controller-from-another-controller__1553251021', 'Nice  Guy', 'admin', 0, 0, 1, '<p>You can render a view in a controller from another controller like so:</p><pre><code>$this -&gt; render( Controller/View );</code></pre>Rendering a view in a controller from another controller', 1, 293, 'CakePHP', 0, 0, '2019-03-22', '2022-01-03'),
(17, 1, 0, 'Cakephp  - How Do I Set A Default Value In An Input Field', 'cakephp-how-do-i-set-a-default-value-in-an-input-field__1553251649', 'Nice  Guy', 'admin', 0, 0, 1, '<p>You add it in the array like so:</p><pre><code>echo $this-&gt;Form-&gt;input( email ,[ default =&gt; enter your email address ]);</code></pre>', 1, 252, 'CakePHP', 0, 0, '2019-03-22', '2022-01-03'),
(18, 1, 0, 'Ajax Append Instead Of Replace', 'ajax-append-instead-of-replace__1553252274', 'Nice  Guy', 'admin', 0, 0, 1, '<p>replace with javascript&nbsp;</p><pre><code>document.getElementById( cvenumbers-ids ).innerHTML = opt;</code></pre><pre><code>$( #results ).html(myHtml);</code></pre><p>append with jquery</p><pre><code>$( #results ).append(myHtml);</code></pre><p>remove with jquery</p><pre><code>$( #results ).remove();</code></pre>', 1, 300, 'Javascript ,JQuery', 0, 0, '2019-03-22', '2022-01-03'),
(19, 1, 0, 'Cakephp Select Which Fields Display In The List Query When Want To Use It In A Drop Down', 'cakephp-select-which-fields-display-in-the-list-query-when-want-to-use-it-in-a-drop-down__1553262759', 'Nice  Guy', 'admin', 0, 0, 1, '<p>The best way i think is</p><pre><code>$thisaray = $this-&gt;Themodel-&gt;find( list , [ keyField  =&gt;  another_id ,  valueField  =&gt;  anotherfield ]);</code></pre>', 1, 235, 'CakePHP', 0, 0, '2019-03-22', '2022-01-04'),
(20, 1, 0, 'Php Using Strtotime() To Compare Two Dates', 'php-using-strtotime-to-compare-two-dates__1553341370', 'Nice  Guy', 'admin', 0, 0, 1, '<p>I have two variables containing strings of dates in the format</p><pre><code>$four_days_have_passed = &#39;07-14-2013&#39;;  $now = &#39;07-10-2013&#39;;</code></pre><p>I have checked the output in FirePHP and the dates are correct.</p><p>Then I try to compare them like this,</p><pre><code>if (strtotime($now) &lt; strtotime($four_days_have_passed))  {    Do Stuff  }</code></pre><p>Why does the code inside the IF statement never execute?</p>', 1, 211, 'PHP', 0, 1, '2019-03-23', '2022-01-03'),
(21, 28, 20, 'answer', 'php-using-strtotime-to-compare-two-dates__1553341370', 'Gabriel Kolbe', 'gabriel-kolbe__1546695864', 0, NULL, NULL, '<p>format is yyyy-mm-dd</p><p>time() give you the current or today&#39;s unix timestamp</p><p>try can convert all dates to unix time stamp before you compare them</p><pre><code>$datetime = \'2012-07-25 14:35:08\';\r\necho strtotime($datetime);</code></pre>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-03-23', '2019-03-23'),
(22, 28, 0, 'In Python The Error I Get Is “inconsistent Use Of Tabs And Spaces In Indentation” How Can I Fix This?', 'in-python-the-error-i-get-is-aoeinconsistent-use-of-tabs-and-spaces-in-indentationa-how-can-i-fix-thisij__1553605872', 'Gabriel Kolbe', 'gabriel-kolbe__1546695864', 0, 0, 1, '<p>Tabs and spaces are two different characters which are rendered as whitespace on screen. The problem is that there is no agreement on how wide a tab character must be, so some editors show it as occupying as much space as 8 spaces, some show it as occupying width of 4 and some 2, and it&rsquo;s also configurable.</p><p>When you indent in python, python just expects that indentation in first line should be the same as indentation in rest of the lines, be it 4 spaces, 1 space, 1 tab, or whatever.</p><p>So when you code and one line is indented with a tab and another with spaces, python gives error, despite the fact that visually in the editor it looks fine (but it won&rsquo;t look fine anymore if you change the width of a tab and double it, now it will look like the tab lines are indented two levels).</p><p>Hence it is suggested that you use either only tabs or spaces. Though it&rsquo;s not really possible to do this when editing someone else&rsquo;s code because we don&rsquo;t know what they&rsquo;ve used.</p><p>One way to combat this error is to go to the settings of your text editor and enable the &ldquo;convert tabs to spaces&rdquo; feature which automatically replaces the tab character with n space characters, n being the tab width your editor uses.</p><p>In the python IDLE editor, you may use Edit &gt; Untabify Region to convert any tabs to spaces.</p>', 1, 239, 'Python', 0, 0, '2019-03-26', '2022-01-04'),
(23, 1, 0, 'Php Date In Format Yyyy-mm-dd To Month, Day And Years In Words ', 'php-date-in-format-yyyy-mm-dd-to-month-day-and-years-in-words__1553871768', 'Nice  Guy', 'admin', 0, 0, 1, 'I have a date like 2018-02-28 and I want it in readible words. How do I convert it?', 0, 227, 'PHP', 0, 1, '2019-03-29', '2022-01-03'),
(24, 28, 23, 'answer', 'php-date-in-format-yyyy-mm-dd-to-month-day-and-years-in-words__1553871768', 'Gabriel Kolbe', 'gabriel-kolbe__1546695864', 0, NULL, NULL, '<p>Use the PHP&nbsp;<code>date</code>&nbsp;function to reformat it:</p><pre><code>echo date(\'F j, Y\',strtotime($row[\'date\']));  </code></pre><p>This will give you February, 28th 2018</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-03-29', '2019-03-29'),
(25, 28, 0, 'Link To A File In Cakephp 3 To Make A File Downloadable Like A Pdf', 'link-to-a-file-in-cakephp-3-to-make-a-file-downloadable-like-a-pdf__1558704428', 'Gabriel Kolbe', 'gabriel-kolbe__1546695864', 0, 0, 1, '<p>You do it like so</p><pre><code>&lt;?php echo $this-&gt;Html-&gt;link( mypdf ,  /pdf/mypdffile.pdf , [ class  =&gt;   ,  target  =&gt;  _blank ]); ?&gt;</code></pre>', 0, 301, 'HP,HTML,PHP', 0, 0, '2019-05-24', '2022-01-03');
