INSERT INTO `user_articles` (`id`, `user_id`, `name`, `slug`, `displayme`, `short`, `content`, `source`, `tags`, `twittercount`, `hitcount`, `rank`, `created`, `modified`) VALUES
(8, 56, 'Understanding The Difference Between AEPS and UPI Transaction', NULL, 1, 'AePss is the acronym for Aadhaar Enabled Payment System the same for UPI as Unified Payment Interface. They are both used for digital payment?services an initiative by NPCI (National Payment Corporation of India) to ensure Cashless society under the ', 'What AePS Service and UPI is about\r\n\r\nAePss is the acronym for Aadhaar Enabled Payment System the same for UPI as Unified Payment Interface. They are both used for digital payment?services an initiative by NPCI (National Payment Corporation of India) to ensure Cashless society under the digital India program.\r\nHere we explain both the subject like what they are, daily benefits in life and usage. Foremost we begin with the UPI transaction.\r\nKeep in touch on fascinating facts on UPI transactions.\r\n\r\nUPI Transaction and Benefits\r\nAs learned above UPI is also known as Unified Payment Interface a digital payment service drive by NPCI to ensure that India is digitally secured.\r\nBefore we begin UPI Transaction I would like to ask, if you have ever heard of UPI?\r\nReminding you, ever used Pay Tm?\r\nMaybe you recount this service now; indeed I am explaining the function same way as\r\nUPI transaction.\r\nThe main objective behind the initiative is competing with mobile online payment platforms such as e-wallets with a bank supported network. UPI is the real-time payment system based on IMPS facilities; used basically for instant money transfer?between banks.\r\nWhat are the benefits of UPI transaction, how can you apply it in your daily use?\r\n\r\nBenefits of UPI\r\nThe platform is the cheapest way to make transfers\r\nSave you the stress of carrying physical cash\r\nDoes not require a bank account\r\nThe best alternative to the POS machine\r\nUsage is safe and secure\r\nReal-time money transfer infrastructure\r\nIdeally, there are ?benefits of using UPI transactions in daily life. This service can be used in the PayTM wallet by transferring money directly without further details.\r\n\r\nAbout AEPS Service and Benefits\r\n\r\nA form of payment system that enables payment for a cashless transaction with the use of credit or debit cards. AEPS service is also supported by NPCI (National Payment Corporation of India) with the aim developing a cashless society under the digital India program.\r\nAEPS service enhances basic banking activities such as cash deposit, withdrawal, cash transfer and balance inquiry using aadhaar card and fingerprint as authentication. The facilities can be used anywhere as long as your bank details are connected to the aadhaar card.\r\nThe AEPS service ensures cashless transactions without the use of debit or credit cards. No need to remember any pin or code; just your 12 digit aadhaar card numbers to the dealer and fingerprint as authentication to carry out basic banking activity.\r\n\r\nBenefits of AEPS\r\nBenefits of AEPS to your daily life includes\r\nCash Deposit\r\nCash Withdrawal\r\nFund Transfer\r\nBalance Inquiry\r\nThe service is beneficial to our daily life for cashless activities. If you are unable to go bank or ATM for a transaction, this service will be of great assistance in rendering excellent basic banking transactions.\r\n\r\nConclusion\r\nIn conclusion, the two most popular digital payment services in India were discussed, what they actually are, how it can be used and its daily life impact. With the recent volume of banking activities, these methods of payments are way too important to overlook.', 'https://steemit.com/aadhaar/@adokhai/understanding-the-differentiating-between-aeps-and-upi-transaction', 'UPI,AEPS,transaction', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-10-15', '2019-10-15');
